  "definition": "Refers to the speed at which items are processed in a hopper (1 item every 8gt, or 2.5 items per second). Usually written as an integer (e.g. \"3x hopper speed\").\n## Common hopperspeeds\n1x: 9000 items/hr\n2x: 18000 items/hr (dropperspeed)\n4x: 36000 items/hr\n6x: 54000 items/hr\n8x: 72000 items/hr",
